sql:
SELECT 
    (SELECT AVG(capacity) FROM events WHERE status = 'planned') AS average_planned_capacity,
    (SELECT AVG(capacity) FROM events WHERE event_format = 'in-person') AS average_in_person_capacity;

SELECT DISTINCT et.type_name
FROM events e
INNER JOIN event_types et ON e.event_type_id = et.type_id;

SELECT trainer_name
FROM trainers
WHERE rating = (SELECT MAX(rating) FROM trainers);

external_knowledge:
Completed events refer to events with a status of 'completed';
The average satisfaction rating is calculated based on user feedback in the 'event_attendance' table;
The rank is determined by the average satisfaction rating in descending order.
